		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Alane Salierno Mason</strong></span> is a book editor in New York City. She translated, as a labor of love, Elio Vittorini&rsquo;s magnificent short novel <em>Conversations in Sicily</em> (New Directions). &ldquo;The Exegesis of Eating&rdquo; was selected for <em>Best Spiritual Writing 2001</em>, edited by Philip Zaleski, and will also appear in <em>We Begin with Food</em>, an anthology of Italian American women writing on food, forthcoming from the Feminist Press.</p><a href="/contributors/alane-salierno-mason" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
